1. f4 {It's the last round of the finals of the SGA Rapid Teams event. We're
playing Raadsheer and only need 2 board points to win the divison. I'm playing
against Liam Clark, Magda's boyfriend. I've indulged in my usual mild trashtalk
before Round 3: \"What were your results so far?\" \"Win draw win\" \"But we've
only played 2 games.\" \"Yeah I'm counting this one.\"} 1... Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. e3
Bg7 4. d4 O-O 5. Bd3 d6 6. Nbd2 c5 7. c3 Nc6 8. O-O Rb8 9. Qe1 cxd4 10. exd4 e5
11. fxe5 dxe5 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. Qxe5 Nd7 {Also defends the rook on b8, but it's
a very flimsy defense.} 14. Qf4 (14. Qg3) 14... b6 15. Bc4 {Pressure on f7.}
15... Qe7 16. Ne4 {Intending Nd6 or Ng5.} 16... Bb7 17. Ng5 Nf6 18. b3 (18.
Bxf7+ {Was already possible.} 18... Rxf7 {Gives up a rook} 19. Qxb8+ Rf8) 18...
h6 19. Nf3 {Darpok move, should've kept attacking.} 19... Kh7 20. a4 {Intending
Ba3 skewering.} 20... Nh5 21. Qd2 {A waiting move, hoping he blunders the
skewer.} 21... Rfe8 {He does not.} 22. Ba3 {At this point I saw he has a queen
trade available, and started calculating the endgame. But he had other ideas.}
22... Qc7 23. Bxf7 {A nice find. Black can't take back. Liam looks puzzled and
then impressed.} 23... Bxf3 {Interesting decision, gives us a rook. I think the
bishop is scarier though and choose to take back.} (23... Qxf7 24. Ng5+ hxg5 25.
Rxf7) 24. Rxf3 (24. Bxe8 Bxg2 25. Bxg6+ Kxg6 26. Qxg2+) 24... Nf6 {Still
choosing not to save the rook. Time pressure maybe.} 25. Bxe8 Ng4 26. Bxg6+
{Desperado grabbing an extra pawn? Or a sac that leads to forced mate?} 26...
Kh8 {Liams sees something I don't.} (26... Kxg6 27. Qd3+ Kg5 (27... Kh5 28. Qf5+
Kh4 29. Rh3#) 28. Qf5+ Kh4 29. Rh3#) 27. Qf4 {Allowing a queen trade now that
I'm up in material. For some reason I also think the c3 pawn is hanging but I
get a knight in return.} 27... Qxc3 {Liam thinks the pawn is hanging too. Gives
up a knight, a rook and a queen in a single move.} 28. Rxc3 {[%c_effect
g1;square;g1;type;Winner;animated;true] Resignation.} (28. Qxb8+ Qc8 29. Qxc8+
Bf8 30. Qxf8#) 1-0

