1. f4 {This is my second game with Henri Korver. I won the first one with a
pretty fantastic Greek Gift sacrifice.} 1... d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. d4 c5 5.
c3 b6 6. Bd3 Be7 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. O-O {Henri has been playing all of his moves
quite fast. I haven't built up any time advantage, even though the opening is
somewhat familiar to me.} 8... Ba6 9. c4 {Lengths I'm going to to avoid trading
my light bishop.} 9... dxc4 10. Nxc4 Nc6 11. Be2 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Nxd4 13. exd4 Rc8
14. b3 Bb7 15. Bb2 Nd5 16. Qd2 Bb4 17. Qd3 Qh4 18. Qe4 Rc7 (18... Nc3 {I thought
this was better.} 19. Qe5 (19. Qe3 Nxe2+ 20. Qxe2)) 19. a3 Bc3 20. Rac1 Bxb2 21.
Nxb2 Nc3 (21... Rxc1 {A missed simplification.} 22. Rxc1 Nxf4) 22. Qe3 Nxe2+ 23.
Qxe2 Rfc8 24. Qd2 Qd8 {Time pressure has arrive for both of us, but Henri is
determined to play fast and keep going.} 25. Nc4 b5 26. Ne5 Rxc1 27. Rxc1 Rxc1+
28. Qxc1 f6 29. Nf3 {I realize at this point that I've blundered a pawn in the
endgame. We'll keep playing though, I want to test him out with 10 seconds on
the clock.} 29... Bxf3 30. gxf3 Qxd4+ 31. Kg2 {I stopped writing the moves here
but I remember everything being scary symmetric after he blunders the pawn on
e6. We end up trading queens on f5, resulting in symmetric pawns and the kings
fighting for opposition. I'll make up some moves 31-43 to see if I can get
there.} 31... a6 32. b4 h6 33. Qc8+ Kh7 34. Qxe6 Qd3 35. Kg3 Qg6+ 36. Kh4 Qg2
37. Qe4+ Qg6 38. Qd5 Qg2 {Somewhere around here Henri offers me a draw. It's the
obvious result but I still want to poke him a bit so I decline.} 39. Qe4+ Qg6
40. Qc6 (40. Qd5) (40. Kh3) 40... Qf5 41. Kg3 g6 42. Qe4 Kg7 43. Qxf5 gxf5 44.
Kh4 Kg6 45. Kg3 Kg7 46. h3 {Completely symmetric now and nothing to play for.}
46... Kf7 47. Kf2 Ke6 48. Ke3 Kd5 49. Kd3 Kd6 50. Kd4 {For a second I think I'm
winning just cos opposition.} 50... Kc6 51. Kc3 Kd5 52. Kd3 {[%c_effect
d5;square;d5;type;DrawBlack;animated;true,d3;square;d3;type;DrawWhite;animated;true]}
1/2-1/2

[Event "SGA Rapid Teams"]
