[Result "1-0"]
[TimeControl "900+10"]

1. f4 {It's the finals of the SGA Rapid Team finals, being held at Amsterdam
West. Mouhanad and I are playing Board 3/4, with Mouhanad exclusively playing
Black and me exclusively playing White.} 1... d5 {I ask my opponent to write her
name down and when she hands my book back, I notice that I'm playing with Maria
Dam, the woman everyone was talking about cos she won 9/9 rounds in the league
stage. I'm nervous but I remember thinking her opponents were a bit weak too. I
do have a shot.} 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. d4 e6 5. c3 Nc6 6. Bd3 {So far I'm
pretty happy, this is a familiar setup for me.} 6... cxd4 7. exd4 Bd6 8. O-O O-O
9. Ne5 Ne4 10. Nd2 f5 {First genuine departure from what the Birdwall. This
annoying move blunts my d3 bishop and makes Qg4 harder.} 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. Bc2
Qb6 13. Qh5 {A blunder, this gives up a pawn.} 13... Nxe5 14. fxe5 Bxe5 15. Rb1
Bd7 16. Qh4 Rf6 17. Bg5 Rg6 18. Be3 Rf8 19. Qe7 {I've been looking for this move
for a while. Dreams of Bxe3.} (19. dxe5 Qxe3+ 20. Qf2 Qxf2+ 21. Rxf2) 19... Bc6
20. b3 {Regretted this soon after playing it since Bb3 seems so much more on
theme with the attack.} 20... Bf6 {Blunders some pawns back. Black's moves are
affected by time pressure from this point on.} 21. Qxe6+ Kh8 22. Rxf5 Qc7 {A
tame move, but Black now has under a minute left.} 23. Bf4 {Seemed like the
obvious move to me but is it a blunder.} 23... Qb6 (23... Qd8 {Black has set up
a discovery check to win the queen. White must defend.} 24. a3 (24. Qd6 Bxd4+
25. Qxd4 Qxd4+ 26. cxd4 Rxf5) 24... Bxd4+ 25. cxd4) 24. Re1 (24. Bxe4 Re8 25.
Qf7 Rxe4) 24... e3 25. Bg3 Qa5 {Maria immediately starts shaking her head. I'm
not 100\% sure I would've seen this if she had just remained stone faced.} 26.
Rxa5 {Handshake.} 1-0

