1. e3 {Papa is visiting and he suggested we play a game of chess. I am naturally
thrilled. We set up a board on the kitchen island. No clock, but I am
annotating. I regret not annotating the last two games we played, the first of
which was on the day I first visited Noida home to meet Noor's family. I won by
trapping his queen and then taking far too long to convert.} 1... d6 {Chicken.}
2. c3 Nf6 3. Na3 g6 4. Bb5+ c6 5. Bf1 {Strange.} 5... Bg7 6. b4 O-O {Papa does
not approve of castling so this is a bit of a cheeky move. In previous game he
has not allowed it. This time he lets it slide.} 7. h3 e5 8. Nf3 Bf5 9. Qb3 Be6
{Tempo tricks.} 10. Qb2 Nbd7 11. b5 Rc8 {I wouldn't mind an open file.} 12. h4
Nc5 {Eyeing the d3 royal fork. If only I can get rid of White's light squared
bishop.} 13. bxc6 Rxc6 {Open file yum yum.} 14. Nb5 a6 15. Na3 {Papa played a
lot of \"knight on the rim\" moves in this game.} 15... Nfd7 {I'm thinking of
playing e4 and Ne5, to get that royal fork anyway.} 16. Qb4 {Queen moves to a
different square that coincidentally still works for the royal fork.} 16... Qc7
{This is needed cos without it white can counterattack on my queen.} (16... e4
17. Nd4 Ne5 18. Nxc6 Ned3+ 19. Bxd3 Nxd3+ 20. Ke2 Nxb4 21. Nxd8 Rxd8) 17. Nb1
{Papa still trying to make the knights more useful.} (17. Ng1 e4 18. Nh3 Ne5)
17... e4 18. Nh2 Ne5 {This is the moment of truth. Queen needs to be moved.} 19.
Ba3 {Papa moves his bishop again and I know I've won.} 19... Ncd3+ {\"Meri game
hi khatam kar diti tussi?\"} 20. Bxd3 Nxd3+ 21. Ke2 Nxb4 22. Bxb4 Bc4+ 23. Ke1
a5 24. Ba3 Rc8 25. Ng4 Bd3 26. h5 Bxc3 {Conversion is everyone's favourite stage
of the game. I will now be saccing everything I have to open up my queen rook
battery.} 27. Nxc3 Rxc3 28. Bc1 {Mistake. Papa had spotted that taking the rook
loses a bishop (or ends in mate), but he accidentally moves it to a square where
it dies anyway.} (28. dxc3 Qxc3+ 29. Kd1 Qc2+ 30. Ke1 Qe2#) 28... Rxc1+ 29. Rxc1
Qxc1# {[%c_effect
g8;square;g8;type;Winner;animated;true,e1;square;e1;type;CheckmateWhite;animated;true]
A totally accidental checkmate.} 0-1

