1. f4 {Board 3 against Oosten-Toren 3 in SGA Rapid Teams. I have been permitted
to play White all 3 games today.} 1... d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 Bf5 {I dislike seeing
this move as it forces me to play quite unnaturally. No Birdwall, just regular
old Bird.} 4. b3 Nc6 5. Bb5 {A gentle probe. If he ignores, he's in trouble.}
5... Bd7 {Also annoying, cos my very natural Ne5 is now a blunder.} (5... e6 6.
Ne5 Bd6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Bxc6+ Kf8 9. Bxa8) (5... g6 6. Ne5 e6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8.
Bxc6+ Nd7 9. Bxa8 Qxa8) 6. d4 (6. Ne5 {Mistake.} 6... Nxe5 7. Bxd7+ Nexd7
{Recaptures!}) 6... a6 7. Be2 Ne4 {Opportunistic.} 8. c3 Bf5 9. Bd3 e6 {Many
things to be done. Bb2 and Bc2 pull back and THEN Nbd2 to avoid losing a
piece/pawn.} 10. Bb2 (10. Nbd2 Nxc3 11. Qc2) 10... Nxc3 {Opponent promptly loses
his mind and throws away a piece for nothing. He's hallucinating a different
line entirely where Black can sac this knight cos there's a white one on d2,
meaning Black can play Bxd3, win back the piece and prevent castling.} 11. Bxc3
Bxd3 12. Qxd3 Nb4 13. Bxb4 Bxb4+ 14. Nc3 {All this trading can't be good for his
chances.} 14... Rc8 15. O-O O-O 16. Ng5 g6 17. Rac1 Qf6 18. e4 c5 19. exd5 Qxd4+
{A surprising offer.} 20. Qxd4 cxd4 21. Ne2 {Big mistake. Allows drawing
opportunitites.} (21. Nce4 exd5 22. Rxc8 Rxc8 23. Nf6+ Kg7) 21... d3 22. Nd4 Bc5
23. Nf3 Rfd8 24. Rcd1 Rxd5 25. Rxd3 Rcd8 26. Rfd1 f6 27. Kf1 e5 {Beautiful,
quiet move that wins back a piece. There is no good place for the knight to go.}
28. fxe5 fxe5 29. Nxe5 {No take me instead.} 29... Rxe5 30. Nf3 Rxd3 31. Rxd3
Rf5 32. Ke2 Bb4 {I stopped writing moves a while ago. The game remains
materially equal but we're both playing with under a minute left with quite a
crowd watching. I'm trying to regulate my breathing a bit and I think he is too.
He cracks first. I am waiting for a knight discovery check to win a rook, and
that's exactly what happens. I see it immediately and play it, then sit back
pretending like the game is over, because it is. Opponent thinks for a while
then resigns.} 1-0

