1. f4 {Rapid Club Teams Tournament in De Raadsheer. I've missed the first two
rounds cos my captain forgot to tell me the date of the event. Fortunately I was
at Sourbh's housewarming that evening, which is just 2mins away from De
Raadsheer. Cycled down on Magda's bike to fill in the last seat for Round 3.}
1... d5 {It's 15+10 and I'm definitely the only person in the room writing down
my moves. 10 seconds is a lot.} 2. Nf3 c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. exd4 e6?!
{[%c_effect e6;square;e6;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 6. c3 Nf6 7. Bd3 Be7
8. Nbd2 Qc7 9. Ne5 Bd7 {Thought it was strange to give up a bishop like this.}
10. O-O O-O-O?? {[%c_effect c8;square;c8;type;Blunder;persistent;true] Pretty
simple one-move blunder.} 11. Nxf7! {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] Lots of headshaking from my
opponent.} 11... Rhf8 12. Nxd8 Bxd8 13. Qf3 g6 14. b3 Nh5 15. Nb1?! {[%c_effect
b1;square;b1;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Ugly move but I think it's
necessary to hold on to the pawn. I don't want to play g3.} 15... e5 16. Qxd5
{Another pawn blundered. Realizing that my opponent maybe isn't a very strong
player. He is dropping low on time (I'm still very close to 15min) and I think
he might be put off by my writing down the moves.} 16... exf4?! {[%c_effect
f4;square;f4;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 17. Bb5? {[%c_effect
b5;square;b5;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Silly idea, not sure why I was trying
this.} 17... a6 18. Be2 {This is better, threatens to win another pawn.} 18...
Be7? {[%c_effect e7;square;e7;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Opponent doesn't
seem to care about pawns anymore.} 19. Bxh5 gxh5 20. Qxh5 Bd6 21. Ba3 {Hell bent
on trading pieces right now.} 21... Ne7 22. Qh6 {Delayed the trade by one move
to threaten a rook and bishop.} 22... Nf5 {A natural defense. Protects both
attacked pieces and attacks queen.} 23. Bxd6! {[%c_effect
d6;square;d6;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] Proud of this find. I didn't mind a
queen trade, but this will be better for me.} 23... Qxd6 {Invites a queen trade,
since taking with the knight would drop a rook.} (23... Nxd6) 24. Qxf4 {I'm up
so many pawns.} 24... Qg6 25. Nd2 Rg8 {These seem like very simple threats.} 26.
Rf2 Nd6 27. c4 {Aiming to kick.} 27... Bh3 28. Qf3 {Just calmly defending. My
opponent is playing purely on increment now, so I just need to wait for him to
make a mistake.} 28... Nf5 {He makes it immediately.} 29. Qxh3 Kb8 30. Qxf5
{Down 11 points in material, this is now extremely resignable, but my opponent
thinks he should play on for tricks etc, which I respect. Except I'm still
writing moves so it's a little tedious for me.} 30... Qg7 {Lol, allows a queen
trade.} 31. Qe5+ Qxe5 32. dxe5 Re8 33. Nf3 Kc7 34. Re1 Re6 35. Ng5 Re7 36. Rf7
{Just resign my guy.} 36... Rxf7 37. Nxf7 Kd7 38. e6+ Ke7 {At this point I very
deliberately closed my book and put the pen down and squared up to play some
bullet moves. This is maybe the sign of confidence he was waiting for cos he
resigned two moves later.} 39. Nh6 b6 40. Nf5+ {[%c_effect
g1;square;g1;type;Winner;animated;true] Finally a handshake.} 1-0

