b7;square;b7;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 15.
Ba4+ $6 {[%c_effect
a4;square;a4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] I
hadn't seen this but it doesn't seem bad.} 15... Bd7 16. Bxd7+ Nxd7 17. Bg5 Nc7
{Two pawns now under attack.} 18. Qe4 $6 {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 18...
Nf6 $6 {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Easy
defense.} 19. Bxf6 Bxf6 20. Rb1 $6 {[%c_effect
b1;square;b1;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 20...
Qxd5 {Now up two pawns.} 21. Qxd5 {I don't understand why White would trade
queens here, but opponent said he didn't see how he could hold on to it.} (21.
Qe3) 21... Nxd5 22. O-O Kd7 23. Nd2 Kc6 {King performing an epic monarch march
across the board to go take of this silly pawn by himself.} 24. Nb3 Kb5 (24...
c4) 25. Ra1 $6 {[%c_effect
a1;square;a1;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 25...
Bxb2 {Third pawn.} 26. Ra2 Bf6 {Realized I have no need to take risks. Up three
pawns, remember $2} (26... Ba3 $6 {[%c_effect
a3;square;a3;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 27. c3
c4 28. Nbd4+ Kc5) 27. a6 {Why do this, the pawn loses a defender like this}
27... Nc7 {Black about to go up yet another pawn.} 28. Ra5+ Kb6 29. Rc1 c4 {Know
what's better than a pawn $2 A piece.} 30. Ra4 cxb3 {For some reason I thought
about this move for some 10 minutes. I genuinely wasn't sure if it was worth the
trouble. Yes I win a piece but my king might get exposed or even trapped on the
edge of the board. Obstructing the bishop is also possible.} 31. Rxb4+ Kc5
{Handy find.} (31... Kc6 32. cxb3+ Kd7 $1 {[%c_effect
d7;square;d7;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 33. Rb7
{I thought this loses the knight.}) (31... Kxa6 32. Rxb3 h6 $2 {[%c_effect
h6;square;h6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 33. c3 $2
{[%c_effect
c3;square;c3;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]}) 32. Rxb3
Nxa6 {FIVE PAWNS} 33. Rcb1 Rab8 {And now the trades can begin. I was in another
room when my opponent came to find me and resign on the spot.} 0-1

