1. f4 {I'm playing Arne in Round 3 of Paul Keres 2026 in Utrecht. I took a bye
in the first two rounds. Arne is a future teammate, and he plays the Bird ! We
are going to be friends.} 1... d6 {Sticking to my usual today.} (1... e5 {I
hovered my hand open the e pawn for a while. I did consider playing the From's
Gambit, but eventually chose not to because I wasn't sure if he uses the
commonly cited 'escape' line of transposing to the King's Gambit. I don't know
how to play that, so I'm not risking it.} 2. fxe5 {He later told me he would've
taken. From's is the only thing he prepped for this match, knowing I play the
Bird too. It's cool, we'll do it next time.}) 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d4 {Arre wah, Arne
transposes to Stonewall too.} 3... g6 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. e4 c5 {So far I am still in
book, and I suspect he is probably not. Who just randomly looks up Austrian
Attack} 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. Bxd7+ Nbxd7 8. h3? {[%c_effect
h3;square;h3;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 8... Qa5?! {[%c_effect
a5;square;a5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] A mistake apparently.} 9. O-O cxd4
10. Qxd4 {I totally forgot he could do this.} (10. Nxd4 Nxe4!! {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;Brilliant;persistent;true] I had this epic sacrifice planned.}
11. Nxe4 Qd5! {[%c_effect d5;square;d5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] Wins back
the piece !} 12. Nxd6+ Qxd6) 10... O-O 11. Kh1? {[%c_effect
h1;square;h1;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Preemptive and thhoda sa darpok.}
11... Nh5! {[%c_effect h5;square;h5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] I got some
kudos for this move later. Forces the queen to go to f2 to stop the fork.} 12.
Qf2 Bxc3 {I thought long and hard before doing this. It is a good bishop after
all. But a pawn is a pawn, and I am planning another sac and trades off Arne's
dark bishop.} 13. bxc3 Qxc3 14. Be3 (14. Rb1 {Thought about this too.} 14...
Rac8) 14... Ng3+? {[%c_effect g3;square;g3;type;Mistake;persistent;true] This is
a sac but the engine dislikes it.} 15. Kg1?? {[%c_effect
g1;square;g1;type;Blunder;persistent;true] Arne sacs a rook ! He wants his dark
bishop.} (15. Qxg3! {[%c_effect g3;square;g3;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}
15... Qxe3! {[%c_effect e3;square;e3;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 16. Rae1
Qc5) 15... Nxe4 {I get another pawn.} 16. Bd4 {This is my biggest miss of the
game. Both queens are attacked. I can go out strong, taking a rook with me.}
16... Nxf2 {Instead I'm just interested in getting to the endgame with those two
extra pawns.} (16... Qxa1 17. Rxa1?! {[%c_effect
a1;square;a1;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} (17. Qe3 Qxa2 18. Qxe4) 17...
Nxf2! {[%c_effect f2;square;f2;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 18. Kxf2 {Easy
sac and now I'm up an exchange.}) 17. Bxc3 Rac8 {Intermezzo I liked. Capablanca
says always go for the open files.} 18. Bd4 Nxh3+?? {[%c_effect
h3;square;h3;type;Blunder;persistent;true] Easily my dumbest moment of the day.
Up two pawns, all I had to do was step back and strap in. But no, this is the
herogiri move. I want to be down a knight but up FOUR pawns.} 19. gxh3 Rxc2 {My
rooks are about to line up. Who can stop four pawns ?} 20. Rf2?! {[%c_effect
f2;square;f2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} (20. Bxa7 b6 21. Rfb1 Ra8 22.
Bxb6! {[%c_effect
b6;square;b6;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 22...
Nxb6 23. Rxb6) 20... Rxf2?! {[%c_effect
f2;square;f2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Trade trade.} 21. Kxf2 Rc8 22. f5
Rc2+ 23. Ke3 Nc5? {[%c_effect c5;square;c5;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 24. f6
e5? {[%c_effect e5;square;e5;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Forces a trade, I
thought.} 25. Bxe5?? {[%c_effect e5;square;e5;type;Blunder;persistent;true] Arne
sacs back. Black is still up 3 pawns.} 25... dxe5 26. Rd1 {Backrank threats.}
26... Rc3+ 27. Ke2 h6?? {[%c_effect h6;square;h6;type;Blunder;persistent;true]
Allows the rook to invade.} (27... Ne6 {This was needed.}) 28. Rd8+! {[%c_effect
