1. f4 {Last game of a very rough SGA season which saw us lose all 7 of our
matches. We're playing VAS 8 in Cygnus Gym. My opponent is 72 years old. My pre
game strategy is to grind.} 1... d5 {Opponents smiles a lot and talks to
himself. Keeps counting things.} 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 b6 {A fianchetto game.} 4. d4
{The puzzled look that many give when they realized you started offbeat but
settled into a boring stonewall.} 4... e6 5. Bd3 (5. Bb5+ {Is maybe more
exciting.} 5... c6 6. Bd3) 5... Be7 6. Nbd2 Bb7 7. O-O O-O 8. Ne5 {Always an
attractive move.} 8... Nbd7 9. Qf3 c5 10. c3 Rc8 11. g4 {Is it too early ?
Engine is fine with it. I'm hoping, as always, for a Greek gift.} 11... g6 {My
opponent has no intention of letting that happen.} 12. Rf2?! {[%c_effect
f2;square;f2;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Strange
looking move, but I want to give my knight a route out and this rook lift will
help if my other rook wants to come to f1.} 12... cxd4? {[%c_effect
d4;square;d4;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (12...
Nxe5) 13. exd4 (13. cxd4 ☒ {Opponent told me after the game that he thinks I
should have played this, but I never like giving up an open file so easily.})
13... Nxe5? {[%c_effect
e5;square;e5;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 14. fxe5
Nd7 15. Nf1?! {[%c_effect
f1;square;f1;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 15...
f6 16. Bh6 Rf7? {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Is a
mistake and white starts to build up a good amount of pressure.} (16... fxe5 17.
Bxf8! {[%c_effect f8;square;f8;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 17... Qxf8 18.
Qe3 Qd8) 17. Ng3 (17. g5 {Against the spirit of the position, kills all the
action.} 17... f5) 17... Qe8?! {[%c_effect
e8;square;e8;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 18.
Raf1! {[%c_effect
f1;square;f1;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 18...
Bf8 19. Bg5 (19. Qe3 Bxh6 20. Qxh6 a6 21. exf6) 19... Bg7 20. Qe2 (20. Bxf6 {Was
already possible ! Look deeper Harman.} 20... Bxf6 (20... Nxf6) 21. g5 {The
magic move.} 21... Bxg5 22. Qxf7+! {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 22... Qxf7 23. Rxf7) 20... Qe7 21.
Qc2? {[%c_effect
c2;square;c2;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Major
blunder, gives up all the pressure.} (21. Bxf6 {Interestingly Black must give up
the exchange to avoid losing more material} 21... Bxf6?! {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} (21... Nxf6?! {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 22. g5) (21... Rxf6 22. exf6 Bxf6
23. Nh5!! {[%c_effect h5;square;h5;type;Brilliant;persistent;true]} 23... gxh5
24. g5! {[%c_effect g5;square;g5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 24... Bxg5 25.
Rf7! {[%c_effect f7;square;f7;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 22. g5!
{[%c_effect g5;square;g5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 22... Bxg5 23. Rxf7!
{[%c_effect f7;square;f7;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 21... Rcf8!
{[%c_effect
f8;square;f8;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 22. exf6
Bxf6 23. Bh6 Bg7! {[%c_effect
g7;square;g7;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 24.
Be3?! {[%c_effect
e3;square;e3;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 24...
Rxf2 {Draw offer, very correctly done. I can tell it's equal and I've lost my
advantage. But the man is 72, he is going to struggle under time pressure. I
play on.} 25. Rxf2 Rxf2 26. Qxf2 Qf6 {Man just wants to trade everything, he is
so mentally ready to draw.} 27. Ne2 {I'm in no hurry.} 27... Qxf2+ 28. Kxf2 e5
29. Bb5 (29. Kg3 e4 {A passed pawn in always scary.}) 29... Nf6 30. h3 {I think
at this point we're both under 5 mins. Endgame pressure is on.} (30. dxe5??
{[%c_effect e5;square;e5;type;Blunder;persistent;true]} 30... Nxg4+! {[%c_effect
g4;square;g4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 31. Kf3 Nxh2+! {[%c_effect
h2;square;h2;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} (31... Nxe5+ ☒) 32. Kg2) 30...
Ne4+ (30... e4? {[%c_effect e4;square;e4;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 31. g5
Nh5! {[%c_effect h5;square;h5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 31. Kg2 Nd6 32.
Bd7 Kf7 33. Kf1 Ke7 34. Ba4 Nc4 35. Bc1 {Several defensive only-moves.} 35...
Nd6 36. dxe5 Bxe5 37. Bf4?! {[%c_effect
f4;square;f4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Black
could've taken actualy.} 37... Ke6?! {[%c_effect
e6;square;e6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (37...
Bxf4 38. Nxf4 Kf6) 38. Nd4+ {Looks nice but doesn't achieve much.} 38... Bxd4!
{[%c_effect
d4;square;d4;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 39. cxd4
Ba6+ 40. Ke1 {Reasoning that both knight entry points are covered.} 40... Bb7
{Defensive move, shows you how nervous he is.} 41. Kd2 {Still confident I have
the knight covered.} 41... a6?! {[%c_effect
a6;square;a6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 42. h4
b5 43. Bxd6 {Honestly just played because I wanted to slightly reduce the
complexity of the endgame time scramble. Knights are way harder to calculate
than bishops.} 43... Kxd6?! {[%c_effect
d6;square;d6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 44.
Bb3 Bc8 45. Bd1 a5?! {[%c_effect
a5;square;a5;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 46.
Ke3? {[%c_effect
e3;square;e3;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (46. g5
Bf5 47. Kc3) 46... Ke6? {[%c_effect
e6;square;e6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Apparently
the game changing blunder, although my opponent thinks it happened several moves
later.} (46... h6 47. Kf4 (47. b4 axb4?! {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 48.
Kf4 Be6 49. Bc2 b3 (49... Bf7 50. g5))) 47. Kf4! {[%c_effect
f4;square;f4;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 47...
h6?! {[%c_effect
h6;square;h6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 48.
Bc2 Kf6 49. g5+! {[%c_effect
g5;square;g5;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] I can
feel the initiative now.} 49... hxg5+ 50. hxg5+ Kf7 51. Ke5 {White king has
invaded and can slowly pick off pawns.} 51... Bb7 52. a3 b4 53. axb4 {Just
clearance.} 53... axb4 54. Bb3 {White will finally win a pawn.} 54... Ke7 55.
Bxd5 Bc8 56. Bg8 Bf5 57. d5 Kf8 58. Be6 {I am enjoying this bishops dance and
struggle.} 58... Bc2 59. Kf6 Bb3?! {[%c_effect
b3;square;b3;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]
Blunders another pawn.} 60. Kxg6 {Took my time with this move, even though we're
both now playing with 1min and under on our clocks. \\\"Do I want another pawn ?
Yeah I do.\\\"} (60. d6 {Was the other move i considered and it also works.})
60... Ke7 61. Kh7 Kf8 62. g6 {Almost a red carpet to promotion.} 62... Bc2?!
{[%c_effect c2;square;c2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Pinned !} 63. Kh6
{Unpinned ! Carpet is back and the pawn is unstoppable. I lean back and my
opponent raises his hand to shake mine. Game lasted 3.5hrs, it was the longest
game of the match. My opponent openly blamed some people in the room who were
being noisy at a critical stage of the game, and to be fair that is what caused
him to make that mistake. But so what, concentration is part of it.} 1-0

[Event "Bentinckstraat Buurman Game"]
[Site "Amsterdam"]
[Date "2026.03.25"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Harman Singh"]
[Black "Bram Willemse"]
[Result "1-0"]
[TimeControl "-"]

1. f4 {I'm at Bram's place for our regular scheduled casual chess game. He has
brought some conveniently sliced pizza and tea. We talk about multitools and
Multatuli.} 1... c5 {An uncommon but principled response to the Bird.} 2. Nf3 e6
{Unusual but nothing wrong with it that I can see.} (2... Nf6 3. e3 e6) 3. e3
Nf6 4. d4 d5 {Quite a mature move I thought. The c pawn is defended, so why
react at all $2} 5. c3 Be7 6. Bd3 Nc6 7. Nbd2 b6 {Bram is playing very well I
think. Pieces are all developing nicely. This bishop fianchetto was maybe
planned back when e6 was played.} 8. O-O O-O 9. Ne5 {Too soon $2} 9... Bb7 10. Qf3
a5 11. g4 {Too soon $2} 11... Qc8 12. g5 {A very rushed attack, the game has only
just begun.} 12... Ne8 $2 {[%c_effect
e8;square;e8;type;Mistake;size;100%2525;animated;false;persistent;true] This is
a mistake, it allows White to do the Greek Gift sac.} (12... Nxe5 {This was
needed.} 13. fxe5 (13. dxe5)) (12... Ne4 {Loses a pawn but stays in the game.})
13. Bxh7+ $3 {[%c_effect
h7;square;h7;type;Brilliant;size;100%2525;animated;false;persistent;true] Always
my favourite move.} 13... Kxh7 14. Qh5+ Kg8 {Eval is still equal even though
White has sacrificed a piece and has a scary queen. But Black is way harder to
play.} 15. Rf3 f6 $4 {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Blunder;size;100%2525;animated;false;persistent;true] Game
ending blunder. Mate is now unstoppable.} 16. g6 $3 {[%c_effect
g6;square;g6;type;Brilliant;size;100%2525;animated;false;persistent;true] Second
piece sacrifice of the game.} 16... Rf7 17. Qh7+ Kf8 18. Qh8# {[%c_effect
g1;square;g1;type;Winner;animated;true,f8;square;f8;type;CheckmateBlack;animated;true]
Quick one.} 1-0

[Event "First game with Henk's Indian chess set"]
[Site "Amsterdam"]
[Date "2026.04.17"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Harman Singh"]
[Black "Henk van Veelen"]
[TimeControl "-"]
[Result "1-0"]

1. f4 {Henk bought a very cool chess set when he was in India, with beautiful
weighted pieces that self-stabilize when you try to tip them over. This is the
first game with the set, played after dinner at Henk's place. He made mac and
cheese and a roasted cauliflower salad.} 1... d5 {A perfectly principled move.}
2. Nf3 Nc6 3. e3 f6 {First genuinely unusual move. Robs the black knight of its
obvious development square.} 4. d4 e5 {I thought this just loses a pawn but the
engine likes it.} 5. fxe5 Bb4+ $2 {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (5...
fxe5 6. dxe5 Bg4 7. Be2) 6. c3 {\"Yeah I should've seen that coming\"} 6... Ba5
7. exf6 $6 {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (7. b4
{Would've been nice, locks up the bishop.}) 7... Qxf6 $6 {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (7...
Nxf6 {Was probably better, allows castling.}) 8. Bd3 Nge7 9. O-O O-O 10. e4 b6 $2
{[%c_effect
b6;square;b6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 11. e5 $1
{[%c_effect
e5;square;e5;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 11...
Qe6 12. Bxh7+ $3 {[%c_effect
h7;square;h7;type;Brilliant;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Greek
gift. An unusual one, cos Black is better off not taking the bishop. Usually
taking is good.} 12... Kh8 (12... Kf7 $6 {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 13. Ng5+) (12... Kxh7 13. Ng5+ $1
{[%c_effect
g5;square;g5;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]}) 13.
Ng5 Qh6 $2 {[%c_effect
h6;square;h6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (13...
Rxf1+ 14. Qxf1 Ba6 {Only way the game goes on.}) 14. Rxf8+ Ng8 15. Rxg8#
{[%c_effect
g1;square;g1;type;Winner;animated;true,h8;square;h8;type;CheckmateBlack;animated;true]
Nice, cagey checkmate.} 1-0

