pieces.} 12. Be2 Bxe2? {[%c_effect e2;square;e2;type;Mistake;persistent;true]
Black declines the imbalance and changes his mind completely.} (12... Nxe3 13.
Bxd3 Nxf1 14. Bxf1 {Black was right to decline.}) 13. Qxe2 Be7 14. Ne5 Ngxe5 15.
fxe5 O-O 16. e4 Qb6 17. Rb1 Nxe5? {[%c_effect
e5;square;e5;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Didn't see this, but it isn't so
bad.} 18. exd5! {[%c_effect d5;square;d5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 18...
Ng6 19. bxc4 exd5 20. Rxb5 (20. cxd5 {Apparently grabbing the pawn is better,
