1. f4 {Round 3 of the tournament. My opponent is young and rated similarly to
me. He lost his first game and drew the second against Rens Mors.} 1... Nc6
{He's confused by my first move but is trying not to show it.} 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3
Bg4 4. d4 Nf6 5. c3 Ne4 6. Bd3 f5 {I'm always annoyed by this move because it
means I have to contend with either a knight or a pawn on e4.} 7. O-O e6 8.
Nbd2?! {[%c_effect d2;square;d2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 8... g5?!
{[%c_effect g5;square;g5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 9. fxg5? {[%c_effect
g5;square;g5;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 9... Nxg5 ☒ 10. Qe1 ☒ Qf6 ☒ 11.
Nxg5! {[%c_effect g5;square;g5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 11... Qxg5 12.
Qg3? {[%c_effect g3;square;g3;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} (12. e4 {Looks like
I'm losing a pawn but not really, cos discovery.} 12... fxe4 (12... dxe4 13.
Nxe4 Qg6) 13. Nxe4 Qe7 14. Nf6+) 12... O-O-O ☒ {I'm convinced at this point that
this is a mistake and I shall be winning a piece.} 13. h3 ☒ {Wins a piece right
?} 13... Bd6 {Nope.} 14. Nf3?! {[%c_effect
f3;square;f3;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Lucky to have this resource, I
hadn't seen it earlier. My opponent will try to hold on the queens and also
avoid losing a piece.} 14... Qg8 (14... Bxg3 15. Nxg5 Bh5 16. Nxe6) 15. Qh4 {A
draw appears on the horizon. Black can just keep attacking my queen and I can't
really avoid it. I'm fine with a draw I guess.} 15... Be7? {[%c_effect
e7;square;e7;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 16. Qh6 Bf8?! {[%c_effect
f8;square;f8;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 17. Qh4? {[%c_effect
h4;square;h4;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 17... Be7 18. Qh6 Bxf3 {My opponent
does not want a draw. Respect.} 19. Rxf3 Bg5?! {[%c_effect
g5;square;g5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 20. Qh5 Qg7 21. Rg3 Rdg8 22.
Kf2?! {[%c_effect f2;square;f2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 22... Qf6 23.
Rf3? {[%c_effect f3;square;f3;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 23... Bh4+ ☒ (23...
Rg6 {Apparently wins the game. White cannot save the queen.}) 24. g3?!
{[%c_effect g3;square;g3;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] I offer a draw as I
play this, but my opponent brushes it off.} 24... Rg5?? {[%c_effect
g5;square;g5;type;Blunder;persistent;true] And plays this move within a second.
He thinks he's trapped my queen, but he's actually blundered a bishop.} 25. Qxh4
{White is now decidedly up, but the queen is still very close to getting
trapped. It'll stay this way for many moves.} 25... Ne7? {[%c_effect
e7;square;e7;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Coming to attack the queen.} 26. e4!
{[%c_effect e4;square;e4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 26... h6 {Very
creative resource. Taking the rook now would trap the queen.} 27. exf5 {I have
to be careful because there are so many ways my queen can die, including
discovered checks.} (27. Bxg5 hxg5 {Queen trapped.} 28. Qg4 {But not really ! I
didn't see this.} 28... fxg4 29. Rxf6 gxh3 30. Rh1) 27... exf5 28. g4 {Finally
giving my queen an exit square.} 28... c5 29. Bxg5 {Cashing in.} 29... hxg5 30.
Qg3 {Safe, but still passive.} 30... f4 31. Qg1 {Hubert has just entered the
room. He can see I'm winning but that my pieces are passive. He sticks around to
watch the rest of the game.} 31... cxd4 32. Rc1 Kb8 33. Kg2 dxc3 34. Rxc3 d4 35.
Rc4 Rd8 36. Qc1 Nc6 {Fork coming up on e5, possibly unavoidable.} 37. Rc5 {I
make my peace with it. Can still win.} 37... Ne5 38. Rxe5 (38. Bf5 Nxf3) 38...
Qxe5 39. b4 {So painfully passive. Just trying to trade queens.} 39... Qd5 40.
a3 Re8 41. Kf2? {[%c_effect f2;square;f2;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 41...
Qa2+?! {[%c_effect a2;square;a2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 42. Qc2 Qxa3?!
{[%c_effect a3;square;a3;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 43. Bg6 ☒ {Seems to
win a rook but actually just forces a trade and the games turns into a
theoretical draw.} (43. Qc5 Qa1) 43... Re3 44. Rxe3 dxe3+ 45. Ke2 {I'm feeling
good but the position is equal. My opponent keeps offering draws but I refuse.
We are under time pressure now and I hope to hold my nerve.} 45... Qxb4 46. Qd3
Qb2+ 47. Kf3? {[%c_effect f3;square;f3;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Huge
blunder, allows a check and a passed pawn.} 47... a6 ☒ (47... Qf2+ 48. Ke4 Qg2+
49. Kf5 Qd2 50. Ke4 Qxd3+ 51. Kxd3 {Would've been death.}) 48. Qf1?! {[%c_effect
f1;square;f1;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Avoiding the check on f2.} 48...
Qc3?! {[%c_effect c3;square;c3;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 49. Bd3 Qc6+
50. Be4 Qc3 51. Qe2 b5? {[%c_effect b5;square;b5;type;Mistake;persistent;true]}
52. h4! {[%c_effect h4;square;h4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] Finally showing
some initiative.} 52... gxh4 53. Kxf4 Qc7+?! {[%c_effect
c7;square;c7;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 54. Kxe3 Qc5+ {Black should just
keep checking.} 55. Kf4?! {[%c_effect
f4;square;f4;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 55... Qc1+? {[%c_effect
c1;square;c1;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 56. Qe3 Qc7+ 57. Kg5 Qe7+?!
{[%c_effect e7;square;e7;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 58. Kh5 h3?
{[%c_effect h3;square;h3;type;Mistake;persistent;true] Stops the checks ! I have
an opportunity.} 59. Qb6+! {[%c_effect
b6;square;b6;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 59... Kc8 {A very easy mate here
that I missed.} 60. Qxa6+ (60. Bf5+ {Can't believe I didn't spot this. WIns the
queen in one move.} 60... Qd7 61. Qc6+ Kb8 62. Bxd7) 60... Kd8 61. Qa8+ Kd7?!
{[%c_effect d7;square;d7;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 62. Qd5+?!
{[%c_effect d5;square;d5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Not ready to trade
just yet.} 62... Kc8 63. Bf5+? {[%c_effect
f5;square;f5;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 63... Kc7 {Up till this moment I've
been calculating if my bishop can stop both pawns if the queens get traded. But
now I see a chance to win the pawns, which would make trading queens a no
brainer.} 64. Qxb5 {Feels passive and I am worried about perpetuals that I don't
see, but it doesn't happen.} 64... h2 {Pretty hopeless move tbh. Now i trade and
win.} 65. Qa5+ {My opponent makes an illegal move here, which neither of us even
notice, since we both know I'm about to trade queens. He plays Kd8. I Game goes
Qa8 Kc7, Qa7 Kd6, Qxe7 Kxe7 and I finally play the vital Be4 to safeguard the
promotion square. Impossible to mess this up now.} 65... Kd6? {[%c_effect
d6;square;d6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 66. Bg6??
{[%c_effect
g6;square;g6;type;Blunder;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] This move
didn't actually happen, I'm just putting it in to fix the illegal move issue.}
66... Kd7 ☒ 67. Qa7+ Kd6 68. Qxe7+ Kxe7 {Queen trade on the correct square.} 69.
Be4! {[%c_effect e4;square;e4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] And this move
actually did happen, except the bishop was coming from f5.} 69... Kf6 70. Kh6
Kf7 71. g5 Kg8?! {[%c_effect g8;square;g8;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 72.
Kg6 Kh8 73. Kf7 {This is quite cool, this isn't a stalemate cos Black still has
a pawn that can (and is now forced to) promote.} 73... h1=Q (73... h1=R) 74.
Bxh1 {And this capture gives Black a square to go to !} 74... Kh7 75. g6+ Kh8
{75th move and we both have finished our scoresheets. We wait while the arbiter
runs to get us another page. I am within my rights to stop the clock, but we've
built up a few minutes now so I'm not stressed.} 76. g7+ Kh7 77. g8=Q+ Kh6 78.
Qg6# {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;Winner;animated;true,h6;square;h6;type;CheckmateBlack;animated;true]
This game has last 4 hours and 15 minutes. It's my longest game ever, and it is
a win.} 1-0

