1. f4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. e3 Bg7 4. b3 {I lose my mind here and decide to play
something I never do in blitz games. Some strange decision to not show my
Stonewall hand too early and stick to Bird-Larsen. There's nothing objectively
wrong with it, but it causes me to take myself out of book, and I spend the rest
of the game trying to return to familiar ground.} 4... Ne4 {A brave move IMO, so
early in the game.} 5. d4 c5 6. Bd3 {Creative defense.} 6... d5 7. Bb2 Nc6 8.
Nbd2 {Desperately want to get rid of this knight.} 8... Qa5 {This ruins me
psychologically. I start giving up piece to return to normality.} 9. Bxe4 dxe4
10. Ne5 cxd4 {White should stop here, accept the pawn loss and just castle out
of trouble. Instead, I blunder a piece on the 11th move.} 11. exd4 e3 {Mentally
I am beyond beaten.} 12. Nc4 {If anything could make things worse, it is this. A
basic miscalculation of tempo, cos I thought I was somehow holding on to the
piece.} 12... exd2+ 13. Nxd2 {And this dumbass recapture means that a piece
remains pinned.} 13... O-O 14. O-O Rd8 15. Nc4 Qc7 16. c3 b5 17. Ne5 {Allows a
trade unfortunately.} 17... Bb7 18. Qe2 b4 19. f5 {I am reduced to playing for
tricks. Game has lasted less than 75 minutes.} 19... Nxe5 20. dxe5 bxc3 21. Ba3
Rd2 {Sigh. Brutal.} 22. Qxd2 cxd2 23. Rad1 Rd8 24. Bb4 Qb6+ {Seriously, why am I
even still playing ? Whom does this serve ?} 25. Rf2 Qxb4 26. f6 exf6 27. exf6
Bh6 28. Re2 Qd4+ 29. Rf2 {Yet another pin permitted.} 29... Be3 30. g4 Bxf2+ 31.
Kf1 Bh4 {Sets up a mate on f2.} 32. Re1 {As a last act on generosity, I gift my
opponent a rare pawn under-promotion mate.} 32... Qf2# {Which he ignores.}
(32... dxe1=Q#) (32... dxe1=R#) 0-1

[Event "Daniel Noteboomtoernooi"]
[Site "Leiden"]
