1. e4 {I'm playing in a 6-round classical tournament in Leiden. Took a bye in
the first round and this is the second. My opponent is a 10 year old kid who
seems ruthless over the board but quite charming after the game.} 1... d6 2. d4
g6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. h3 Nbd7 6. Be3 c6 7. Be2 Qa5 {Playing this now seems
a bit early, since White could easily castle kingside, but so could I.} 8. Nd2
{Protects the e4 pawn twice.} 8... O-O {Definitely too soon.} 9. f4 e5 10. fxe5
dxe5 11. Nc4 Qc7 12. dxe5 Nxe5 13. Qd6 {Inviting a queen trade so early in the
game makes me feel like the kid is fond of long drawn endgames. I can't avoid it
either, or I'll lose my knight.} 13... Ne8 {Setting up nicely for the endgame.}
14. Qxc7 Nxc7 15. Bf4 Nxc4 16. Bxc4 Bxc3+ 17. bxc3 {Doubled pawns, so now I just
want to trade everything.} 17... Ne6 18. Bxe6 Bxe6 19. Bd6 Rfd8 20. e5 Bd5 21.
Kf2 f6? {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Absolute
goofball move. I think I'm winning a pawn.} 22. Be7 {Missed this entirely. I'm
not just losing a pawn, I've also gifted him a passed pawn AND an outpost.}
22... Rd7 23. Bxf6 Rf8 24. Kg3 Be4?! {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 25.
e6? {[%c_effect
e6;square;e6;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Sacrifices
the bishop, and it is a mistake, but I don't see the response.} 25... Rd6 ☒
{[%c_effect d6;square;d6;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]
Practically loses the game.} (25... Rd2 {Was better. White can advance pawns but
it won't help.} 26. e7?! {[%c_effect
e7;square;e7;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 26...
Rxg2+ 27. Kh4 Re8! {[%c_effect
e8;square;e8;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (27...
Rxf6 28. e8=Q+)) 26. Be7! {[%c_effect
e7;square;e7;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 26...
Rxe6 27. Bxf8 Kxf8 28. Rae1 Re7 29. Rhf1+ Ke8 30. Rf2 Bd5 31. Rxe7+ Kxe7 32. a3
b5 33. Rf4 a5 34. Kf2 a4 35. g4 Ke8 36. Ke3 Ke7 37. Kd4 Kd6 38. Rf6+ Ke7 39. g5
Be6 40. Rxe6+ {I was right, the kid loves endgames. He has calculated that this
is already winning for White because of how advanced the king is. Very
impressive IMO.} 40... Kxe6 41. Kc5 Kd7 (41... Kf5) 42. c4 bxc4 43. Kxc4 Kd6 44.
Kb4 c5+ 45. Kxa4 Kc6 46. Ka5 c4 47. Kb4 Kd5 48. a4 {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;Winner;animated;true] I resigned. We didn't analyse but only
because it was really late. I know f6 was the losing move anyway.} 1-0

