1. f4 {Willy was 5 mins late. He told me he would be but Jim insisted we start
the clocks at 8pm.} 1... d5 {It's a similar opening to our last game in Best of
the West, which Willy won.} 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 Nf6 4. d4 Be7 5. Bd3 O-O 6. Nbd2
Nbd7?! {[%c_effect
d7;square;d7;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 7. O-O
c5 8. c3 a6 9. Ne5 b5 10. Qf3 {Gives me the option of Qh5 or Qh3 later.} (10.
Nc6) (10. g4?! {[%c_effect g4;square;g4;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Thought
about it, to set up a Greek gift, but it's probably too early for such
shenanigans.}) 10... g6?! {[%c_effect
g6;square;g6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] No more
Greek Gift. Willy avoided it in our last game too. I think he'll always look for
it when we play.} 11. b3 (11. Nc6 {I did see this move, wins me the bishop pair.
But the bishop looked kind of bad to me, and what does one do with a bishop pair
anyway ?}) 11... Bb7 12. Bb2 Nxe5?! {[%c_effect
e5;square;e5;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 13.
fxe5 {I'm usually happy to see this trade because it makes my rook better.}
13... Nh5 14. Qg4?! {[%c_effect
g4;square;g4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Willy
said he didn't like the look of this, and the engine agrees with him. Qh3 might
be better, but I wanted to do a rook lift.} 14... Rc8 15. Rf3 c4 16. Bc2?!
{[%c_effect
c2;square;c2;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (16.
bxc4 dxc4 {I thought this was bad because it's a discovered attack on a rook.
But there is a defense.} 17. Be4! {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) (16. Rh3? {[%c_effect
h3;square;h3;type;Mistake;persistent;true] I considered this because I thought
it's a simple counter attack on the knight. But really it robs the queen of an
escape square, and now I'll lose a piece.} 16... f5! {[%c_effect
f5;square;f5;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 17. exf6 (17. Qf3? {[%c_effect
f3;square;f3;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 17... cxd3! {[%c_effect
d3;square;d3;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 17... Nxf6 18. Qxe6+ Kg7) 16...
b4?! {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Looks
scary but it wasn't hard to handle.} 17. bxc4! {[%c_effect
c4;square;c4;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 17...
dxc4 18. Rh3?! {[%c_effect
h3;square;h3;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] What I
wanted to play anyway.} 18... Ng7?! {[%c_effect
g7;square;g7;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Willy
saw this as the only defense. Didn't think of attacking the restricted queen.}
(18... f5 19. exf6! {[%c_effect f6;square;f6;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}
19... Nxf6 20. Qxe6+ Rf7) 19. Be4?! {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] A
cowardly move. Both of us have good bishops and this move will force us to give
them away.} 19... Bxe4 ☒ {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} (19... Qd7?
{[%c_effect d7;square;d7;type;Mistake;persistent;true]}) (19... Qa5 {Oof engine
line.} 20. Bxb7 bxc3) 20. Nxe4 bxc3? {[%c_effect
c3;square;c3;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 21. Bxc3
f5 22. exf6! {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true] En
passant actually forced.} 22... Bxf6 23. Nxf6+?! {[%c_effect
f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Long
think here. I'm seeing a line that never happens.} (23. Rf1?! {[%c_effect
f1;square;f1;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Was the other candidate, but it
allows Black's knight back in the game so good I didn't play it.}) 23... Qxf6
(23... Rxf6?! {[%c_effect f6;square;f6;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] What I
thought he'd play for some reason.} 24. d5 {Discovery.} 24... Rf7? {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 25. dxe6! {[%c_effect
e6;square;e6;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} (25. Bxg7 Rxg7 26. Qxe6+!
{[%c_effect e6;square;e6;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 25... Re7?!
{[%c_effect e7;square;e7;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]}) 24. Rf3 {Going to
fight for the f file naturally.} 24... Qe7 25. Raf1 {Holding on to the f file.}
25... Rxf3 26. Qxf3 {I know as I play this that this move is going to take us
straight into the endgame. All major pieces off the board and comparable kings.
Black has a passed pawn. But White has central pawns facing an isolated one.
We're both down to 3min each. I like my odds a bit, especially with the time
pressure.} 26... Rf8 27. Qxf8+ {Played quickly. Let's go.} 27... Qxf8 28. Rxf8+
Kxf8 29. Kf2 Ke7 30. e4 (30. d5?! {[%c_effect
d5;square;d5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true] Was missed, but I thought it was a
win.} 30... Nh5?? {[%c_effect h5;square;h5;type;Blunder;persistent;true]
Terrible move, knight is trapped.} (30... Kf7?? {[%c_effect
f7;square;f7;type;Blunder;persistent;true]} 31. Bxg7 Kxg7 32. d6 {Can't believe
this loses} (32. dxe6 Kf6 33. Kf3! {[%c_effect
f3;square;f3;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 33... Kxe6 34. Ke4! {[%c_effect
e4;square;e4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]})) 31. d6+ Kxd6 32. g4! {[%c_effect
g4;square;g4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]}) 30... Nh5? {[%c_effect
h5;square;h5;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Wrong
idea, knight should be going the other way.} 31. Kf3 ☒ {[%c_effect
f3;square;f3;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] To defend
f4.} (31. Bd2 {Why ? Idk, I guess defends f4. I'm too scared to unblock that
pawn.}) 31... Nf6 32. h3 {I want to move my king to e3, but that might lose a
pawn.} (32. Ke3? {[%c_effect e3;square;e3;type;Mistake;persistent;true]} 32...
Ng4+ 33. Kf4 Nxh2) 32... h5 33. Ke3 Nd7? {[%c_effect
d7;square;d7;type;Mistake;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 34. Ba5 ☒
{[%c_effect a5;square;a5;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]
Thought this was necessary to advance the d pawn.} (34. d5 {I didn't like the
look of this because of the line I saw next.} 34... exd5?! {[%c_effect
d5;square;d5;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 35. exd5 Kd6 36. Kd4! {[%c_effect
d4;square;d4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 36... Nb6 {And I thought this
loses a pawn. But I missed the check.} 37. Bb4+! {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true]} 37... Kd7) 34... Nb8 ☒ {[%c_effect
b8;square;b8;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true]} 35. d5 exd5
36. exd5 Kd6 37. Kd4 Nd7 38. Bb4+ {Spite check.} 38... Kc7 39. Kxc4 {Feeling
confident now.} 39... Ne5+ 40. Kc5?? {[%c_effect
c5;square;c5;type;Blunder;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Apparently
a blunder. Knight has an easy route to picking up a pawn. Big lesson here, the
tempo from the check allows the knight to invade.} (40. Kd4 Nd7) (40. Kc3) 40...
Nd3+ 41. Kc4! {[%c_effect
c4;square;c4;type;GreatFind;size;100%25;animated;true;persistent;true]} 41...
Nxb4 ☒ {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;Miss;size;100%25;animated;false;persistent;true] Bad decision
here. Black had to hold on the knight and keep fighting.} (41... Nf4 {Wins a
pawn easily.}) 42. Kxb4 Kd6 43. Kc4 g5 {Both of us are looking to exhaust our
moves now, to force zugzwang. White will get there first.} 44. g4 hxg4 45. hxg4
a5 46. a4 {Zugzwang !} (46. a3 a4 47. Kd4 Kd7) 46... Ke5 {Took my time to
calculate here. White needs one babysitter move and 3 pawn moves to queen. Black
need 3 moves to capture the g pawn, 1 move to get out of the way, and THEN 4
moves to queen.} 47. Kc5 Kf4 48. d6 {No longer writing down moves. Easy
conversion from here.} 48... Kxg4 49. d7 Kh3 50. d8=Q g4 51. Qh8+ {Spite check.}
51... Kg2?! {[%c_effect g2;square;g2;type;Inaccuracy;persistent;true]} 52. Qg8
{Faster mates are possible of course.} 52... g3 53. Qxg3+ {Kill the spirit.}
53... Kxg3 {[%c_effect c5;square;c5;type;Winner;animated;true]} 1-0

