1. f4 {I finished last season with a slightly silly loss to Lennart, so I'm
looking forward to some revenge. We're playing the same colours and I think we
might be repeating a lot of the same moves from last time.} 1... Nf6 2. Nf3 g6
3. e3 Bg7 4. d4 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nbd2 {It's the same game till here.} 6... c5
{First sign that Lennart has prepped a bit for me. c5 is common.} (6... Nc6
{What he played last time.}) 7. c3 b6 {Lennart proudly told me later that he
knew this was \"the best move\", which is a slightly ignorant thing to say 7
moves in IMO. There are not single right moves for players at our level at this
stage of the game. Also he's wrong, cos b6 is definitely not what the engine
told him to do. He is remembering a line where White has already castled, and b6
just helps fianchetto a bishop.} 8. O-O Ba6 {Remained annoying for a long long
time.} 9. c4 {Very unusual response, first time I've ever played it. Engine
doesn't like it, but Lennart couldn't find what to do against it.} 9... Qc7
(9... cxd4 10. Nxd4) 10. Qe2 {Adds a defender to the weakening c4 pawn.} 10...
Rd8 (10... Rc8 {I thought this seemed more natural.} 11. dxc5 Qxc5 12. Nb3 Qc6)
11. Ne5 Nbd7 12. Qf2 {I'm having dreams of Nxe5.} 12... dxc4 (12... Nxe5 13.
fxe5 Ne4 14. Qxf7+ Kh8 15. Qf3 e6 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Bxe4) (12... cxd4 {Simply
wins a pawn. Lennart missed it.} 13. exd4 dxc4) 13. Nexc4 {Thought this was the
only option that held on to the pawn.} (13. Ndxc4 {I thought this was a mistake,
because Black can remove a defender on e5.} 13... Nxe5 14. fxe5 Ng4) 13... Ng4
14. Qe2 {Back to defending.} 14... Ngf6 15. b3 Nd5 {Strange move, but Nc3 looks
annoying.} 16. Bb2 Nb4 17. Be4 Rac8 18. a3 Nc6 19. Rac1 Nf6 20. Bf3 cxd4 {Black
goes up a pawn.} 21. Bxc6 {White must remove a defender to get the pawn back.}
21... Qxc6 22. Bxd4 Qe6 {Threatening Rxd4.} 23. Qf3 Rd7 {This arrangement of
rooks looks sus to me but I couldn't exploit it. g7 bishops helps a lot by
avoiding backrank mates.} 24. Rfd1 Bb7 25. f5 {A puzzling move that I'm very
proud of finding. Lennart is under 2 mins at this point, and I'm still over 5.
I'm playing this move literally just to get him to think and waste time. The
queen trade is losing, and he needs to think to avoid it and just grab the pawn.
He spends almost 40 seconds.} 25... Qd5 (25... Bxf3 {Big mistake. White will end
up a piece or exchange up.} 26. fxe6 Bxd1 (26... Rxd4 27. Ne5 (27. Nxf3 Rxd1+
28. Rxd1)) 27. exd7 Nxd7 28. Rxd1) (25... Qxf5) 26. Qg3 {Just holding on to the
queens to keep the game complicated under time pressure.} 26... Qxf5 {Black now
a pawn up.} 27. Nf3 Rdc7 28. Rf1 Qd7 {A lot of Black's moves now are just
shuffling of pieces, playing on increment.} 29. Rfd1 {Many of my moves are tempo
tricks and time gainers. Just want him to make a big mistake.} 29... Qe6 30. Ng5
Qc6 31. Na5 {A ridiculous move that would never work in a classical game. Black
absolutely does not need to save their queen. Instead sac it, Whites's queen is
on its way soon.} 31... Qd5 (31... Qxc1 32. Rxc1 (32. Qe1 Qxd1 33. Qxd1 Rc1)
32... Rxc1+ 33. Kf2) 32. Bxf6 {Looks like a good move, capturing a piece with
discovered attack on a queen.} 32... Qxa5 {White will now win a rook.} 33. Rxc7
Rxc7 34. Qxc7 Bxf6 35. Qd8+ (35. Qxb7 {Don't know why I didn't see this. Board
blindness basically, and too much eagerness to flag Lennart.}) 35... Kg7 36. Nf3
Qxa3 37. Qd7 Be4 {Strange move but both of us are now shuffling and not really
writing moves.} 38. Qd2 Qxb3 39. Kf2 Bc3 40. Qc1 Qa2+ 41. Kg3 Qb2 (41... Be5+
{Missed this.}) 42. Qxb2 Bxb2 43. Nd4 Ba3 44. Kf4 {Silly move, blunders a pawn
and any chance of stopping Black's kingside army.} 44... Bxg2 45. e4 {Blocks out
the bishop.} 45... a5 46. Nc6 e6 47. Rd2 Bf1 48. Ra2 {Just tempo tricks.} 48...
Bc5 49. Ra1 Bb5 50. Ne5 Ba6 51. Rb1 Bb7 52. Nd7 {Clearly aiming for Nxc5, pinned
pawn.} 52... h5 53. Nxb6 (53. Nxc5 {EASY WIN. Saw it and somehow still missed
it.}) 53... Bxb6 54. Rxb6 Bc8 {Now engine says draw.} 55. Rb8 Bd7 56. Rb7 {White
will keep attacking and Black will released when it's clear he isn't a danger to
k} 56... Bc6 57. Rb6 {[%c_effect
g7;square;g7;type;DrawBlack;animated;true,f4;square;f4;type;DrawWhite;animated;true]
I offered a draw and to my surprise Lennart accepted. He said it was because of
low time, but IMO 10 second increment is enough to play through any endgame.
Black should abandon the a5 pawn and just focus on safely pushing their 4 pawns
vs 2 isolated ones on the kingside. I think him not realizing that and accepting
a draw offer denotes something about the nature of power and intimidation.
Lennart should've kept playing.} 1/2-1/2

