1. e4 {It's schaakfestival in Amsterdam, and I've asked Marjolein to add me to
the simul players against ex Women's World Champion Peng Zhaoqin. She forgot,
but then added a table for me later. Peng tries to play a different opening on
each board and I receive a simple e4.} 1... d6 2. d4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 {Kind of
forgot to play Nf6 here, no other reason.} 4. f4 {GMs and strong players always
play the Austrian against me.} 4... Nf6 5. e5 dxe5 6. fxe5 Nd5 7. Nf3 O-O 8. Bc4
c6 {Weak.} 9. O-O Bg4 10. h3 Be6 11. Bb3 (11. Ng5 Nxc3 12. Nxe6 Nxd1 13. Nxd8
Rxd8 14. Bxf7+ (14. Rxd1 Bxe5) 14... Kh8 15. Rxd1 {Long line that I calculated
for no reason.}) 11... Qb6 {Position from now is very cramped and I feel like
I'm always making forced moves.} 12. Na4 Qc7 13. Nc5 Bd7 14. Qe2 b6 15. Nxd7
Nxd7 16. c4 {A series of ugly knight moves begins.} 16... Nb4 17. a3 Na6 {This
knight is now useless for the rest of the game.} 18. Bf4 e6 19. Rad1 Rad8 20.
Bg5 {Every move makes me uncomfortable.} 20... f6 21. exf6 Nxf6 22. Qxe6+ Kh8
23. Ne5 {Peng blunders here. Her queen can be trapped, and she will need to sac
a knight to keep it.} 23... Rde8 {Missed a chance at a good result against a GM,
sheh.} (23... Rd6 24. Nxg6+ {Only way to hold on to the queen.} (24. Nf7+ Rxf7
25. Qe2) 24... hxg6 25. Qe1) 24. Qxc6 Qe7 25. Rde1 Qd8 26. Bxf6 Bxf6 {I
deliberated for a long time about whether to recapture with bishop or rook. Pend
returned on her round and I asked if I could get more time to make my move. She
said no! \"Play fast, you have to play.\" Surprised, I played bishop just
because I had calculated that rook was bad.} (26... Qxd4+ 27. Kh1 Bxf6 28. Nxg6+
Kg7 29. Rxe8 Rxe8 30. Qxe8) (26... Rxf6 27. Nf7+ {Obviously bad.}) 27. Nf7+
{[%c_effect g1;square;g1;type;Winner;animated;true] Peng explained later that
the recapture method made no difference. I was losing my queen either way. All
the more strange that she didn't allow me extra time to think in an untimed
simul game where mine wasn't the slowest game. Then again I think she had been
told that she was taking too long on her rounds and she was worried at this
point that I might try to keep fighting after losing my queen. I didn't, I
resigned.} 1-0

