1. f4 {Best of the West against Willy Au, a very nervous looking Chinese man who
followed me on instagram before the game. My insta handle is the same as my
lichess username, so I wonder if this means he knows to expect 1. f4. I prepared
From's Gambit just in case, but he says he was surprised by this first move.}
1... d5 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 Nf6 4. d4 Nbd7 {Nc3 is more common, but this is better
for me.} 5. Bd3 Be7 6. Nbd2 O-O 7. O-O c5 8. c3 b6 9. Ne5 Bb7 10. Qf3 {I don't
play this often, but I'm worried about that b7 bishop and I want to keep the e4
hole well defended.} 10... Nxe5 11. fxe5 Ne4 {Willy thought long and hard before
playing this, and eventually decided he was okay with giving up a pawn. The
alternative would've allowed a Greek Gift sacrifice which I had been eyeing for
a while.} (11... Ne8 12. Bxh7+?? {[%c_effect
h7;square;h7;type;Blunder;persistent;true] Engine does not actually approve of
the sacrifice !} 12... Kxh7 13. Qh5+ Kg8 14. Rf3 Bg5 (14... g6 {Is better.}))
12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Bxe4 Bxe4 14. Qxe4 Qd7 15. Qg4 Rac8 16. e4 {Trying to bring my
bishop to h6 and win an exchange.} 16... Kh8 (16... cxd4 {Willy reached out his
hand and almost played this move but stopped himself in time.} 17. Bh6 g6 18.
Bxf8 Rxf8) 17. Be3 {Defending the weak pawn.} (17. d5 exd5) 17... Qb5 (17...
cxd4 18. Bxd4 Bc5 19. Bxc5 Rxc5) 18. Rf2 cxd4 (18... a6 {I'm having dreams of
trading away bishops and forcing his rook away from c8. This would allow me to
sacrifice my queen on e6. He cannot take, cos backrank checkjmate.} 19. dxc5
Bxc5 20. Bxc5 Rxc5 21. Qxe6) 19. Bxd4 {This is weak. I thought a bishop trade
was good for me because I'm a pawn up, but in reality it just hands a valuable
diagonal over to the black queen which will now keep my rook pinned for the rest
of the game.} (19. cxd4 {Much better.}) 19... Bc5 20. Bxc5 Qxc5 21. Rf1 f6
{Seemingly a mistake as it gives up another pawn.} 22. Qxe6 (22. exf6 Rxf6 23.
Qg3) 22... fxe5 23. Qd5 (23. b4! {[%c_effect
b4;square;b4;type;GreatFind;persistent;true] Only move and it would've saced the
game.} 23... Qe3 24. Kh1!! {[%c_effect
h1;square;h1;type;Brilliant;persistent;true] Amazing move, sacrificing the rook
for a quick backrank checkmate.} 24... Rxf2 (24... Qxf2 25. Rxf2 Rxf2 26. Qxc8+)
25. Qxc8+ Rf8 26. Rxf8# (26. Qxf8#)) 23... Rxf2 {Willy sets a trap but I don't
fall for it. Exchanging queens now would've been a disaster.} 24. Rxf2 (24.
Qxc5?? {[%c_effect c5;square;c5;type;Blunder;persistent;true]} 24... Rxf1+ 25.
Kxf1 Rxc5) 24... Qe3 {Keeping the rook pinned. White should focus on solving
that problem.} 25. Qxe5 {Instead I got for more material and this ends the
game.} 25... Rf8 26. Qd4 {Idiotic/Gentlemanly \\\"go ahead, play your
checkmate\\\" move.} (26. h4 {Would've resulted in the loss of a rook. You hold
on to your queen and pray for perpetual.} 26... Qxf2+ 27. Kh2) (26. Qf5 {Saw I
could sac my queen to stay in the game, then COMPLETELY FORGOT ABOUT IT and
ended up playing into checkmate just to be a gentleman.} 26... Rxf5 27. exf5
Qc1+ 28. Rf1 Qxb2 29. f6 gxf6) (26. h3 Rxf2) 26... Qe1+ {Willy started
announcing his moves here. \\\"Check\\\"} 27. Rf1 Qxf1# {[%c_effect
h8;square;h8;type;Winner;animated;true,g1;square;g1;type;CheckmateWhite;animated;true]
\\\"Aaannd checkmate !\\\"} 0-1

[Event "Zwart op Wit"]
