1. d4 g6 2. e4 d6 3. Bf4 {White going for the 150 attack against the Pirc.} 3...
Nf6 4. Nc3 Nbd7 {Unnecessary so soon in the game, but was justified when White
played an early e5.} 5. Nf3 Bg7 6. e5 {Too soon.} 6... dxe5 (6... Nh5) 7. Nxe5
c6 (7... Nh5 8. Be3 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qxd1+ 10. Rxd1 Bxe5 11. Bh6) 8. Bc4 e6 9. Qf3
Nd5 10. Nxf7 {White sacs a knight to extract the Black king. It is scary but
must be accepted.} 10... Kxf7 11. Bxd5 (11. Bc7+ {Discovered checks that don't
win a queen.} 11... Qf6) (11. Bg5+ {Discovered checks that don't win a queen.}
11... N7f6) 11... cxd5 (11... exd5 {Apparently the better move, but I rejected
it because the king felt unsafe.}) 12. Nxd5 {Second knight sac-ed, but this time
I refuse cos too scary.} 12... Nf6 (12... exd5 {Black can apparently take.} 13.
Qxd5+ Ke8 {And Black is surprisingly safe.}) 13. Nc7 Rb8 (13... Bd7 14. Nxa8
Qa5+) 14. O-O-O (14. Nxe6 Bxe6 15. Bxb8 Qa5+) (14. Ne8) 14... Bd7 {Blunder,
makes the d-pawn more powerful.} (14... b5 {Never even considered this. I had
forgotten that these pawns can even move. This gives the rook a way to escape
the x-ray attack and enter the game.}) 15. d5 e5 (15... exd5) (15... Nxd5) 16.
Bxe5 Bg4 (16... Rf8 {A move that was begging to be played all game.}) 17. Qb3
Bxd1 {I played this move thinking white would first take back and then I would
avoid the royal fork by playing Qd7.} (17... Qd7 {Had to be played.}) 18. d6+
{But the royal fork can be played immediately. Black is about to lose a queen
and there's apparently a mate in 19.} (18. Rxd1 Qd7 19. d6+ Kf8 20. Ne6+ Kg8)
18... Kf8 1-0

