1. f4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. e3 g6 4. d4 Bg7 5. c3 Nh6 6. Bd3 d6 7. O-O O-O 8. Qe1
cxd4 9. exd4 Qb6 10. Kh1 {Paranoid.} 10... Re8 11. b3 Bf5 12. Bc4 Rac8 13. Be3
Ng4 14. Bg1 Na5 15. h3 Nf6 16. d5 Qc7 17. Bb5 Nxd5 {Black gives up the exchange
for some extra pawns.} 18. c4 {White doesn't accept, instead offers his own
rook.} 18... Nxf4 {Black in turn refuses, keeps grabbing pawns.} 19. Nc3 Nc6 20.
Rd1 a6 21. Ba4 {I'm playing moves like this one specifically cos it's Joppe, and
I want there to be lots of piece on the board to induce time pressure.} 21...
Qd7 22. Ng5 h6 23. Rxf4 {White missed this under time pressure.} 23... hxg5 24.
Rf2 {Mistake, Rf1 was much better.} 24... Bxh3 25. Nd5 (25. gxh3 Qxh3+ 26. Bh2
Bxc3) 25... Bg4 26. Rdd2 Qd8 {Joppe initially placed the queen on c7 but held on
the piece and noticed the knight. Smiled and moved it to d8. Effects of time
pressure again.} 27. Ne3 {Unnecessary, the knight was happy on d5.} 27... Be6
28. Rf3 Bc3 29. Qf2 Kg7 {Black doesn't need the rook, and White hasn't noticed
the check on h8.} 30. Rc2 Rh8+ 31. Bh2 Be5 32. Ng4 {White gives up a knight for
a measly check, but it doesn't turn into anything.} 32... Bxg4 33. Rxf7+ Kg8 34.
g3 Bf5 35. Rc1 (35. Rxf5 {Saw this move then confused myself out of it.} 35...
gxf5) 35... Kxf7 36. Kg2 Kg7 37. Rh1 Be4+ 38. Kg1 Bxh1 39. Kxh1 {[%c_effect
h1;square;h1;type;Winner;animated;true] I stopped annotating here cos time
pressure, but this game ended with checkmate for Black.} 0-1

